1
00:04:21,862 --> 00:04:27,960
THEY SAY
NOTHING STAYS THE SAME

2
00:05:09,743 --> 00:05:11,609
Thank you.

3
00:05:14,014 --> 00:05:15,311
I'll need a ride back...

4
00:05:16,350 --> 00:05:18,785
at around sunset.

5
00:07:47,201 --> 00:07:48,726
Boatman!

6
00:07:52,739 --> 00:07:53,706
Hurry up!

7
00:07:57,644 --> 00:07:58,770
Move it!

8
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:08,754
Faster, boatman!

9
00:08:10,591 --> 00:08:11,786
Right away.

10
00:08:16,029 --> 00:08:17,463
Hurry!

11
00:08:18,499 --> 00:08:22,231
Thank you for waiting, sir.

12
00:08:23,704 --> 00:08:26,469
Watch it!
You're in my way.

13
00:08:28,942 --> 00:08:30,671
Get going.

14
00:08:30,777 --> 00:08:32,745
Yes, sir.
Right away.

15
00:08:34,114 --> 00:08:36,606
Off we go.

16
00:08:36,717 --> 00:08:38,617
You can barely row!

17
00:08:46,193 --> 00:08:47,718
Give me a ride.

18
00:08:49,129 --> 00:08:51,564
Don't go back.
I'm in a hurry!

19
00:08:51,665 --> 00:08:54,157
I'm sorry, but it's the rule.

20
00:08:54,268 --> 00:08:58,000
What rule?
There are no rules for boatmen.

21
00:08:58,105 --> 00:09:00,073
Just take me across!

22
00:09:02,276 --> 00:09:03,675
Get a move on!

23
00:09:04,711 --> 00:09:06,577
Get in, let's go.

24
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:09,706
Sorry. This thing's so heavy.

25
00:09:09,817 --> 00:09:11,945
Stop fumbling around!

26
00:09:15,756 --> 00:09:18,851
- Sorry to stall you.
- Go, boatman!

27
00:09:19,927 --> 00:09:21,656
Faster, you incompetent fool

28
00:09:27,034 --> 00:09:29,025
You're so clumsy.

29
00:09:36,777 --> 00:09:38,074
Here.

30
00:09:38,178 --> 00:09:39,202
Thanks.

31
00:09:39,313 --> 00:09:41,247
You wasted my time!

32
00:09:42,716 --> 00:09:45,151
I caused you trouble, Toichi.

33
00:09:45,252 --> 00:09:47,118
I delayed you.

34
00:09:48,288 --> 00:09:51,815
What an arrogant man he is!

35
00:09:52,993 --> 00:09:57,226
I don't know him.
Maybe he's from upstream?

36
00:10:00,134 --> 00:10:02,796
I bet he's involved...

37
00:10:03,904 --> 00:10:06,168
in building the bridge.

38
00:10:06,273 --> 00:10:09,072
All that banging is so noisy.

39
00:10:10,244 --> 00:10:13,179
Hey, Toichi,
have you eaten?

40
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,805
Not yet.

41
00:10:14,915 --> 00:10:17,646
I've been ferrying people non-stop.

42
00:10:17,751 --> 00:10:20,777
I got potatoes upstream.
Want some?

43
00:10:20,888 --> 00:10:23,118
Don't worry.
Go home and eat.

44
00:10:23,223 --> 00:10:24,850
It's okay!

45
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:29,156
It's always better to eat with someone.

46
00:10:30,898 --> 00:10:32,992
Let me cook them here.

47
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:34,329
You're so kind.

48
00:10:42,209 --> 00:10:43,870
It's so heavy!

49
00:10:46,713 --> 00:10:48,306
Hey, I want to cross.

50
00:10:48,415 --> 00:10:49,940
Yes, sir.

51
00:11:00,093 --> 00:11:00,924
Get in.

52
00:11:02,763 --> 00:11:04,026
Thank you.

53
00:11:34,695 --> 00:11:36,254
Toichi, here.

54
00:11:36,363 --> 00:11:37,956
Thank you, sir.

55
00:11:38,999 --> 00:11:40,763
Let's see what I shoot.

56
00:11:40,868 --> 00:11:42,302
I'll be back.

57
00:11:42,402 --> 00:11:44,029
Have a nice hunt, sir!

58
00:11:55,315 --> 00:11:57,306
This'll make it even.

59
00:11:57,417 --> 00:11:59,010
What's that?

60
00:11:59,119 --> 00:12:00,348
My passenger...

61
00:12:01,822 --> 00:12:04,154
Nihei gave me them.

62
00:12:04,258 --> 00:12:08,126
That means I won't owe you anymore.

63
00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:09,821
I lost out...

64
00:12:11,265 --> 00:12:13,256
These look better!

65
00:12:21,308 --> 00:12:25,711
Hot potatoes on a hot day
is hellish!

66
00:12:34,388 --> 00:12:36,186
There they go again.

67
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:42,191
Are you okay, Toichi?
Doesn't the noise bother you?

68
00:12:45,165 --> 00:12:47,327
I guess I got used to it.

69
00:12:50,504 --> 00:12:52,268
Not me.

70
00:12:54,374 --> 00:12:56,399
You know, Toichi.

71
00:12:56,510 --> 00:13:01,812
When the noise is unbearable,
I think I'll destroy that bridge!

72
00:13:03,517 --> 00:13:07,385
That bridge will be bad for you, tool

73
00:13:08,989 --> 00:13:13,517
The villagers say
it'll be convenient,

74
00:13:13,827 --> 00:13:17,991
but they're wrong.
I don't think it'll be good.

75
00:13:19,566 --> 00:13:24,197
You've ferried people
over the river for years.

76
00:13:25,339 --> 00:13:29,401
That's how we've always
got upstream.

77
00:13:30,511 --> 00:13:31,979
Why change it?

78
00:13:34,081 --> 00:13:39,019
I know the bridge
will be convenient...

79
00:13:40,287 --> 00:13:44,281
but then we won't need
your boat, Toichi.

80
00:13:44,391 --> 00:13:46,052
That's wrong.

81
00:13:47,594 --> 00:13:49,323
It's just wrong!

82
00:13:56,136 --> 00:13:57,365
Toichi.

83
00:13:58,472 --> 00:14:00,463
Join me.

84
00:14:00,574 --> 00:14:04,238
Let's destroy the bridge
before it's done.

85
00:14:06,313 --> 00:14:09,339
I can't tell if you're fooling.

86
00:14:10,918 --> 00:14:12,443
Me neither!

87
00:14:13,987 --> 00:14:16,046
I'm not very smart.

88
00:17:27,447 --> 00:17:32,146
...so I thought it was a boar!

89
00:17:32,252 --> 00:17:38,316
I was shocked
when he jumped out of the bush!

90
00:17:38,425 --> 00:17:40,484
I'd shoot, too.

91
00:17:41,528 --> 00:17:44,361
Lucky I'm a bad shot.

92
00:17:44,465 --> 00:17:47,765
He'd be dead if I wasn't.

93
00:17:48,068 --> 00:17:50,503
Is he okay?

94
00:17:50,604 --> 00:17:52,402
His ear was scorched

95
00:17:52,506 --> 00:17:56,033
so he was in a daze for a while.

96
00:17:56,143 --> 00:17:57,577
He would be!!

97
00:17:58,746 --> 00:18:03,411
Thank God, he was quicker than a boar!

98
00:21:05,365 --> 00:21:09,529
Damn, that noise!
The fish got spooked.

99
00:21:13,874 --> 00:21:17,401
River hobos!

100
00:21:17,511 --> 00:21:20,742
<i>Get out of here, scum!</i>

101
00:21:20,848 --> 00:21:24,284
Eat this and die!

102
00:21:24,384 --> 00:21:26,648
You brats!
Cut it out!

103
00:21:26,754 --> 00:21:28,620
I'm going to eat you up!

104
00:21:31,024 --> 00:21:33,550
You stupid brats!

105
00:21:36,730 --> 00:21:39,927
Those kids are hopeless.

106
00:21:43,470 --> 00:21:45,495
I want peace and quiet.

107
00:21:54,414 --> 00:21:55,882
We need to cross!

108
00:21:59,820 --> 00:22:01,447
Look at that bull!

109
00:22:01,555 --> 00:22:02,954
Let me help.

110
00:22:04,758 --> 00:22:06,283
Be care full

111
00:22:15,002 --> 00:22:18,632
It'd be easier if there was a bridge.

112
00:22:18,739 --> 00:22:21,674
Come on, this is nothing.

113
00:22:21,775 --> 00:22:23,300
Right, Toichi?

114
00:22:29,650 --> 00:22:31,744
We'll go where the water's shallow.

115
00:22:33,053 --> 00:22:34,885
Come on.

116
00:22:34,988 --> 00:22:36,956
Steady, boy.

117
00:22:38,459 --> 00:22:41,793
- That's the way.
- Good boy!

118
00:22:42,863 --> 00:22:45,355
This way.

119
00:22:45,466 --> 00:22:46,661
Come on.

120
00:22:48,068 --> 00:22:49,866
You can do it.

121
00:22:49,970 --> 00:22:51,665
Let's go.

122
00:22:53,006 --> 00:22:54,701
You okay, Genzo?

123
00:22:58,011 --> 00:23:01,413
- Are you okay?
- Yes, it was no trouble.

124
00:23:02,583 --> 00:23:04,051
We made it!

125
00:23:04,151 --> 00:23:08,554
I thought I was stuck,
but you made it possible.

126
00:23:08,655 --> 00:23:10,487
Your bull got wet.

127
00:23:10,591 --> 00:23:13,754
It'll dry on our way upstream

128
00:23:13,861 --> 00:23:18,355
in this heat!
And its hide is silkier.

129
00:23:18,465 --> 00:23:19,694
Let's go.

130
00:23:27,441 --> 00:23:29,000
It feels nice!

131
00:23:54,601 --> 00:23:56,797
It'll be another hot day.

132
00:25:01,568 --> 00:25:05,129
It's such a desolate village.

133
00:25:05,239 --> 00:25:07,936
There's nothing there.

134
00:25:08,041 --> 00:25:11,739
You from there, Mr. Boatman?

135
00:25:11,845 --> 00:25:13,677
No, I'm not.

136
00:25:13,780 --> 00:25:17,876
I came from another village upstream.

137
00:25:17,985 --> 00:25:19,612
Right.

138
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:23,520
Well, I guess you had
your reasons for leaving...

139
00:25:23,624 --> 00:25:25,991
Something like that.

140
00:25:26,093 --> 00:25:30,553
Right. I knew that was the case.

141
00:25:32,065 --> 00:25:35,194
Don't you want to go back?

142
00:25:35,302 --> 00:25:39,205
I have no family or relatives there.

143
00:25:39,306 --> 00:25:42,071
I don't think I'd belong.

144
00:25:45,312 --> 00:25:47,542
I know what you mean.

145
00:25:51,185 --> 00:25:55,019
Do you know the Chinese
character for loneliness?

146
00:25:56,089 --> 00:25:58,524
Uh... no.

147
00:25:58,625 --> 00:26:02,152
Oh, okay. Never mind that.

148
00:26:03,897 --> 00:26:06,594
Don't be embarrassed.

149
00:26:06,700 --> 00:26:12,537
The character for loneliness
is similar to fox.

150
00:26:14,675 --> 00:26:18,202
There are foxes around here, right?

151
00:26:18,312 --> 00:26:21,612
Foxes, raccoon dogs and even bears.

152
00:26:21,715 --> 00:26:24,207
I bet.

153
00:26:24,318 --> 00:26:25,911
So...

154
00:26:26,019 --> 00:26:30,786
foxes always seem lonely to me.

155
00:26:32,126 --> 00:26:33,719
Isn't that strange?

156
00:26:34,795 --> 00:26:39,858
You're right.
I guess foxes are lonely, too.

157
00:26:43,070 --> 00:26:49,100
Mr. Boatman, I was sold
as a child so my family could eat.

158
00:26:49,209 --> 00:26:52,110
I worked for a medicine maker.

159
00:26:52,212 --> 00:26:56,274
They had many books,
so I learned to read.

160
00:26:56,383 --> 00:26:58,613
Good for you.

161
00:26:58,719 --> 00:27:02,280
I was born very sturdy.

162
00:27:02,389 --> 00:27:04,357
I've never been sick.

163
00:27:06,193 --> 00:27:09,959
I sold medicine,
but I never needed any!

164
00:27:12,132 --> 00:27:17,298
I did okay for a child who was sold off.

165
00:27:20,641 --> 00:27:22,268
Even so...

166
00:27:22,376 --> 00:27:27,177
I've become sentimental
about the old village.

167
00:27:29,349 --> 00:27:32,319
I thought I'd never go back but

168
00:27:33,921 --> 00:27:37,880
I keep thinking about the past lately.

169
00:27:39,026 --> 00:27:40,653
Isn't that funny?

170
00:27:42,396 --> 00:27:45,798
So I went back to the village...

171
00:27:48,068 --> 00:27:52,096
but there's nothing for me there anymore.

172
00:30:59,526 --> 00:31:03,292
What? A kid was drifting
in the river?

173
00:31:03,397 --> 00:31:07,834
The boat hit something
and it was a human.

174
00:31:07,935 --> 00:31:09,869
Let me check.

175
00:31:12,272 --> 00:31:13,865
A person?

176
00:31:13,974 --> 00:31:18,172
I thought she was dead,
but she was breathing.

177
00:31:18,278 --> 00:31:21,179
I did what I could.

178
00:31:23,617 --> 00:31:25,517
What the hell!

179
00:31:25,619 --> 00:31:28,213
I need more mugwort.

180
00:31:28,322 --> 00:31:31,622
Is there any around your place?

181
00:31:31,925 --> 00:31:33,359
Yes, there isl!

182
00:31:34,395 --> 00:31:35,863
So...

183
00:31:37,097 --> 00:31:38,622
I'll get some!!

184
00:31:38,932 --> 00:31:40,024
Thanks.

185
00:31:40,134 --> 00:31:41,431
Okay!

186
00:31:43,070 --> 00:31:45,300
Okay! I'll be right back!

187
00:31:47,107 --> 00:31:49,872
Mugwort. Mugwort, mugwort...

188
00:32:32,586 --> 00:32:34,281
Hey, Toichi.

189
00:32:36,190 --> 00:32:41,219
She looks better.
Her breathing's steadier.

190
00:32:41,328 --> 00:32:43,228
That's good.

191
00:32:43,330 --> 00:32:45,628
Your mugwort medicine worked!

192
00:32:45,733 --> 00:32:47,462
That's right.

193
00:32:48,535 --> 00:32:51,163
It works very well.

194
00:32:51,271 --> 00:32:53,603
She'll be well soon.

195
00:32:54,741 --> 00:32:59,303
But I worry that she hit her head.

196
00:32:59,413 --> 00:33:04,647
You're right.
She was bleeding around here.

197
00:33:05,986 --> 00:33:09,388
We don't know how far she floated.

198
00:33:09,490 --> 00:33:15,020
If she got a bad blow to the head,
mugwort won't help.

199
00:33:43,190 --> 00:33:45,557
Boatman! I need to cross!

200
00:33:45,659 --> 00:33:47,024
Yes, sir.

201
00:33:51,598 --> 00:33:54,329
- Stop fishing!
- I'm sorry.

202
00:33:54,434 --> 00:33:56,061
Hurry up!

203
00:34:00,140 --> 00:34:03,508
You're vain,
that's what you are.

204
00:34:03,610 --> 00:34:08,013
Lay off! I got laid.
That's all that matters.

205
00:34:09,383 --> 00:34:14,014
<i>You splashed me!
Don't rock the boat.</i>

206
00:34:17,658 --> 00:34:19,456
Careful, you idiot!

207
00:35:26,360 --> 00:35:28,795
Bad things happen.

208
00:35:28,896 --> 00:35:31,729
Imagine having your throat slit!

209
00:35:31,832 --> 00:35:37,271
I heard that you squeal
like a wild beast and die.

210
00:35:37,371 --> 00:35:41,569
- You make sounds?
- It's more like air releasing.

211
00:35:41,675 --> 00:35:43,837
It's terrible.

212
00:35:44,144 --> 00:35:47,114
The entire family was killed...

213
00:35:47,214 --> 00:35:49,706
It was some kind of grudge.

214
00:35:49,817 --> 00:35:53,219
Right. He even killed the children?

215
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:56,290
Merciless bastard.

216
00:35:56,390 --> 00:35:59,587
Did you hear about it, Boatman?

217
00:35:59,693 --> 00:36:04,893
No. Only what I heard you say now.

218
00:36:05,199 --> 00:36:06,758
Is that right?

219
00:36:06,867 --> 00:36:10,826
There's a village called Ichi-nomiya,
20 kilometers upstream.

220
00:36:10,938 --> 00:36:12,872
It's a spooky place.

221
00:36:13,173 --> 00:36:15,198
No one told you about it?

222
00:36:15,309 --> 00:36:17,175
Rumors have legs, right?

223
00:36:17,277 --> 00:36:19,473
What happened?

224
00:36:19,580 --> 00:36:23,244
Apparently a whole family was massacred.

225
00:36:23,350 --> 00:36:24,681
Throats slit.

226
00:36:24,785 --> 00:36:28,221
Yes, they were slit, it was savage.

227
00:36:28,322 --> 00:36:31,451
Ichi-nomiya is creepy!

228
00:36:31,558 --> 00:36:33,390
It's horrible.

229
00:36:33,494 --> 00:36:37,795
The killer is at large.

230
00:36:37,898 --> 00:36:40,492
Oh, wait.

231
00:36:40,601 --> 00:36:44,663
I heard that a boy or girl...
is missing.

232
00:36:44,772 --> 00:36:47,833
The killer might have taken one of them.

233
00:36:47,941 --> 00:36:50,603
After killing the rest?

234
00:36:50,711 --> 00:36:56,673
However it went, it's cruel.
Everyone's talking about it.

235
00:36:57,818 --> 00:36:59,183
I see.

236
00:37:11,965 --> 00:37:13,763
Toichi!

237
00:37:13,867 --> 00:37:15,335
She's awake!

238
00:37:16,570 --> 00:37:21,440
She's awake but she won't
say a thing!

239
00:37:21,542 --> 00:37:23,704
She won't answer my questions.

240
00:37:23,811 --> 00:37:25,870
When did she wake up?

241
00:37:25,979 --> 00:37:30,940
A while ago. While you were
taking someone across.

242
00:37:31,251 --> 00:37:32,582
<i>How did it go?</i>

243
00:37:32,686 --> 00:37:36,350
How? She just sprang up!

244
00:37:36,457 --> 00:37:38,653
I was surprised.

245
00:37:38,759 --> 00:37:43,356
I think there was a "Whoa" or "Ugh"|

246
00:37:43,464 --> 00:37:46,434
She said, "Whoa" and "Ugh"?

247
00:37:46,533 --> 00:37:47,898
No, me! I did!

248
00:37:48,002 --> 00:37:52,235
I was so surprised I said, "Ugh"!

249
00:37:52,339 --> 00:37:54,808
I'm not talking about you, Genzo.

250
00:37:54,908 --> 00:37:55,773
Right.

251
00:37:55,876 --> 00:37:59,676
She sprang up and looked around...

252
00:38:02,416 --> 00:38:04,612
Then she stared at me.

253
00:38:04,718 --> 00:38:07,779
Okay. I'll go see how she is.

254
00:38:09,590 --> 00:38:11,752
<i>Toichi, I have to go!</i>

255
00:38:11,859 --> 00:38:13,623
Okay, thank you.

256
00:38:37,518 --> 00:38:38,849
Are you...

257
00:38:40,487 --> 00:38:41,750
okay?

258
00:38:44,725 --> 00:38:46,659
I...

259
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:49,559
I row a boat.

260
00:38:52,533 --> 00:38:54,763
I'm a boatman.

261
00:38:54,868 --> 00:38:56,358
And...

262
00:38:57,805 --> 00:39:00,035
I found you.

263
00:39:01,608 --> 00:39:02,905
So...

264
00:39:05,879 --> 00:39:09,474
you can rest here
until you feel better.

265
00:40:07,141 --> 00:40:08,802
Are you hungry?

266
00:40:09,877 --> 00:40:11,470
Here...

267
00:40:13,013 --> 00:40:14,378
Eat this.

268
00:41:17,778 --> 00:41:22,477
Remember what I told you
about the Ichi-nomiya massacre?

269
00:41:22,583 --> 00:41:28,716
It wasn't the son who was kidnapped.
It was the daughter.

270
00:41:28,822 --> 00:41:30,483
A girl!

271
00:41:31,625 --> 00:41:33,491
Either way it's horrible.

272
00:41:37,197 --> 00:41:41,065
You must ferry across
many people every day.

273
00:41:41,168 --> 00:41:42,829
That's right.

274
00:41:42,936 --> 00:41:46,634
You might have taken the killer!

275
00:41:48,042 --> 00:41:51,137
Watch for anyone with a girl.

276
00:41:51,245 --> 00:41:53,737
When did it happen?

277
00:41:53,847 --> 00:41:56,179
