333
00:54:07,981 --> 00:54:11,645
I need to go across to the village.

334
00:54:12,686 --> 00:54:15,656
I was told I could cross here.

335
00:54:19,026 --> 00:54:21,893
Can you take me there?

336
00:54:21,996 --> 00:54:23,430
Yes, sir.

337
00:54:24,865 --> 00:54:27,459
- Please get in.
- Okay.

338
00:54:31,405 --> 00:54:32,463
You're the boatman?

339
00:54:32,573 --> 00:54:35,804
Yes, sir.
In the center, please.

340
00:54:35,910 --> 00:54:38,845
I thought I'd have to row myself.

341
00:54:45,953 --> 00:54:47,318
Is it hard?

342
00:54:47,421 --> 00:54:48,354
Sorry?

343
00:54:48,455 --> 00:54:51,857
You row the boat every day?

344
00:54:51,959 --> 00:54:53,358
Yes, sir.

345
00:54:57,431 --> 00:55:00,298
It must be tough in this heat.

346
00:55:00,401 --> 00:55:03,894
There's nothing else I can do.

347
00:55:04,004 --> 00:55:08,532
Rowing boats is all I'm capable of.

348
00:55:08,642 --> 00:55:11,805
- You can make a living?
- Sort of.

349
00:55:11,912 --> 00:55:13,505
You get paid?

350
00:55:13,614 --> 00:55:19,712
Yes, sir. I don't charge
the villagers though.

351
00:55:19,820 --> 00:55:23,313
I charge city folk five rin.

352
00:55:23,424 --> 00:55:25,017
Oh, okay.

353
00:55:25,325 --> 00:55:27,521
Pay me when we get there.

354
00:55:29,463 --> 00:55:30,726
