475
01:05:10,344 --> 01:05:12,574
he's no longer a town doctor...

476
01:05:16,250 --> 01:05:21,586
Whatever I say,
you only half-listen to.

477
01:06:36,430 --> 01:06:37,591
Here.

478
01:07:39,059 --> 01:07:42,120
That doctor's got a screw loose.

479
01:07:42,229 --> 01:07:45,130
He needs this bag!

480
01:07:45,232 --> 01:07:49,100
How can he forget something so important?

481
01:07:49,203 --> 01:07:52,571
I think he's a great man.

482
01:07:52,673 --> 01:07:57,736
He comes all the way from town
to see his patients.

483
01:07:57,845 --> 01:07:59,244
Right.

484
01:07:59,346 --> 01:08:01,337
It's really something.

485
01:08:02,383 --> 01:08:05,114
You've got a point there.

486
01:08:05,219 --> 01:08:07,449
We sure owe him a lot,

487
01:08:08,489 --> 01:08:12,221
but it's not good to forget this!

488
01:08:16,163 --> 01:08:20,430
The doctor left in the late afternoon.

489
01:08:20,534 --> 01:08:24,732
We only noticed his bag late at night.

490
01:08:25,772 --> 01:08:30,107
We would've noticed it sooner,

491
01:08:30,211 --> 01:08:35,240
but he put it by a pot
in the dark doorway.

492
01:08:36,417 --> 01:08:39,546
I wonder how he'll work today.

493
01:08:39,653 --> 01:08:41,246
Right?

494
01:08:41,355 --> 01:08:44,848
It'd be strange if he saw
patients without this.

495
01:08:56,603 --> 01:09:01,097
That man's going to deliver
a bag to the doctor!

496
01:09:02,376 --> 01:09:07,212
The doctor did his rounds
here yesterday.

497
01:09:07,314 --> 01:09:10,215
He left his bag at that man's place.

498
01:09:11,585 --> 01:09:15,385
He's a bit of an odd character,

499
01:09:16,490 --> 01:09:17,548
but...

500
01:09:18,659 --> 01:09:20,127
I feel like...

501
01:09:21,428 --> 01:09:24,125
he sees straight through me.

502
01:09:26,900 --> 01:09:30,336
The doctor said he'd come back.

503
01:09:33,307 --> 01:09:38,211
You should talk to him
if you're still in pain.

504
01:09:40,180 --> 01:09:42,615
Do you have any pain?

505
01:09:45,853 --> 01:09:47,321
No.

506
01:09:50,424 --> 01:09:52,449
Okay.

507
01:09:52,559 --> 01:09:53,754
He's a good man.

508
01:09:56,330 --> 01:09:58,890
You should consult him
if you need to.

509
01:10:03,537 --> 01:10:07,565
My job is to help people
cross the river.

510
01:10:09,944 --> 01:10:12,276
You can see that.

511
01:10:12,379 --> 01:10:17,647
Every day, I meet all sorts of people
crossing the river.

512
01:10:17,751 --> 01:10:23,383
It makes me happy
to help out folks a little.

513
01:10:26,460 --> 01:10:27,894
Well...

514
01:10:29,863 --> 01:10:34,198
I guess it means nothing to you.

515
01:10:41,408 --> 01:10:46,676
I thought you went
back home or something.

516
01:10:52,453 --> 01:10:54,251
You didn't go home?

517
01:10:58,993 --> 01:11:00,461
Right.

518
01:11:01,528 --> 01:11:03,462
Do you have anywhere to go?

519
01:11:08,535 --> 01:11:09,900
Right.

520
01:11:10,004 --> 01:11:13,998
Well, I have little to offer,
but you can stay...

521
01:11:16,810 --> 01:11:18,744
as long as you want.

522
01:11:19,947 --> 01:11:24,407
I live alone so you won't be
putting me out.

523
01:11:29,056 --> 01:11:33,789
Toichi, how are you doing?

524
01:11:33,894 --> 01:11:35,589
Genzo!

525
01:11:35,696 --> 01:11:37,027
Going upstream?

526
01:11:38,065 --> 01:11:41,035
No, not today.

527
01:11:47,341 --> 01:11:48,570
She came back?

528
01:11:48,676 --> 01:11:51,737
Yes, last night.

529
01:11:51,845 --> 01:11:53,438
Right.

530
01:11:53,547 --> 01:11:57,814
