01:43:31,312 --> 01:43:36,876
But some folks might find it spooky
to leave a body

832
01:43:36,984 --> 01:43:39,180
<i>to animals to eat.</i>

833
01:43:41,321 --> 01:43:42,720
So Toichi.

834
01:43:43,958 --> 01:43:49,294
I want to do it secretly
So no one knows.

835
01:43:51,699 --> 01:43:54,259
In the night hours...

836
01:43:54,368 --> 01:43:55,802
before the daybreak.

837
01:43:57,538 --> 01:44:00,906
I want to fulfill his wish.

838
01:44:07,715 --> 01:44:09,342
I It's a lot to ask...

839
01:44:11,519 --> 01:44:14,853
but please help me.

840
01:50:52,887 --> 01:50:57,347
Sorry I got you involved in this.

841
01:50:59,293 --> 01:51:01,819
You always helped Dad cross.

842
01:51:03,097 --> 01:51:06,643
With your boat you helped him
carry the lives he was given.

843
01:51:06,667 --> 01:51:09,261
With your boat you helped him
carry the lives he was given.

844
01:51:10,704 --> 01:51:14,766
Dad would've been so happy...

845
01:51:17,077 --> 01:51:19,307
Thank you, Toichi.

846
01:52:00,388 --> 01:52:01,878
Fireflies.

847
01:52:06,327 --> 01:52:08,295
Fireflies...

848
01:52:08,395 --> 01:52:09,829
They're still there.

849
01:52:10,864 --> 01:52:12,332
Yeah.

850
01:52:17,505 --> 01:52:18,215
Maybe one is Nihei's dad's soul departing.

851
01:52:18,239 --> 01:52:23,075
Maybe one is Nihei's dad's soul departing.

852
01:52:26,246 --> 01:52:27,941
I always thought...

853
01:52:29,917 --> 01:52:34,980
Nihei's dad was a great man.

854
01:52:37,491 --> 01:52:42,861
He dedicated his life
to helping others.

855
01:52:45,132 --> 01:52:47,157
How difficult is that.

856
01:52:50,537 --> 01:52:52,198
But me...

857
01:52:53,974 --> 01:52:58,878
I'm helping others.
I like to think I'm doing that but...

858
01:53:00,380 --> 01:53:02,872
I feel they owe me.

859
01:53:04,051 --> 01:53:07,351
I hope the bridge never gets made.

860
01:53:07,455 --> 01:53:10,857
I can't help thinking like that.

861
01:53:10,958 --> 01:53:12,824
I'm full of myself.

862
01:53:15,029 --> 01:53:17,259
But for Nihei's dad...

863
01:53:19,834 --> 01:53:22,269
others came before him.

864
01:53:22,369 --> 01:53:24,337
Even after he died...

865
01:53:26,006 --> 01:53:28,236
he wants to be of benefit.

866
01:53:33,047 --> 01:53:33,289
That's the kind of man...

867
01:53:33,313 --> 01:53:35,077
That's the kind of man...

868
01:53:36,884 --> 01:53:38,545
I'd like to be.

869
01:54:23,197 --> 01:54:25,188
The troubadours!

870
01:54:25,299 --> 01:54:27,097
How festive!

871
01:54:27,201 --> 01:54:29,033
What funny costumes!

872
01:54:32,039 --> 01:54:34,406
I can't wait for the festival.

873
01:54:38,379 --> 01:54:40,939
It's going to be fun.

874
01:54:42,216 --> 01:54:43,360
We heard that the bridge
isn't finished yet...

875
01:54:43,384 --> 01:54:44,852
We heard that the bridge
isn't finished yet...

876
01:54:44,952 --> 01:54:48,115
Thank the Lord for the boatman!

877
01:54:48,222 --> 01:54:51,556
Every year I'm in the festival but...

878
01:54:51,659 --> 01:54:52,990
No bridge.

879
01:54:53,093 --> 01:54:56,085
Builders nowadays are quick!

880
01:54:56,196 --> 01:54:58,961
- They sure are.
- I can't wait!

881
01:54:59,066 --> 01:55:04,197
- It's all about convenience.
- We need a bridge.

882
01:55:04,305 --> 01:55:07,536
It'll be great once we can walk across.

883
01:55:07,641 --> 01:55:10,269
Next year we can do that.

884
01:55:10,377 --> 01:55:12,311
Then we won't get wet.

885
01:55:12,413 --> 01:55:14,643
And it will be quicker!

886
01:55:14,948 --> 01:55:16,109
It'll be great.

887
01:55:16,216 --> 01:55:18,150
It'll be much easier.

888
01:55:18,252 --> 01:55:20,152
My kid hates boats.

889
01:55:20,254 --> 01:55:24,248
- We won't need the boat any more.
- It'll be easier.

890
01:55:24,358 --> 01:55:27,658
- We can cart things over.
- It'll be so easy.

891
01:55:27,962 --> 01:55:30,659
- How convenient.
- I can't wait.

892
01:56:09,270 --> 01:56:12,240
Look. Is that smoke?

893
01:56:12,339 --> 01:56:14,535
- Where?
- You're right!

894
01:56:16,143 --> 01:56:17,406
Is it the bridge?

895
01:56:18,712 --> 01:56:20,339
Isn't it almost done?

896
01:56:24,118 --> 01:56:25,608
I hope it's okay.

897
01:56:38,766 --> 01:56:43,465
...but I know a lot about you.

898
01:56:43,571 --> 01:56:45,539
About me?

899
01:56:45,639 --> 01:56:48,472
I've been watching you.

900
01:56:48,576 --> 01:56:51,341
I'm a ghost and I live here.

901
01:56:51,445 --> 01:56:52,708
That's nonsense.

902
01:56:53,014 --> 01:56:55,346
<i>You don't have to believe me,</i>

903
01:56:55,449 --> 01:56:58,009
but I know a lot about you.

904
01:56:59,186 --> 01:57:01,712
That's why I came lo you.

905
01:57:03,057 --> 01:57:06,721
That girl has the life owed to me.

906
01:57:07,027 --> 01:57:09,394
<i>She was meant to die that night...</i>

907
01:57:10,698 --> 01:57:13,190
and I was lo replace her

908
01:57:13,300 --> 01:57:16,668
<i>while her soul waited to reincarnate.</i>

909
01:57:16,770 --> 01:57:18,568
Reincarnate?

910
01:57:18,673 --> 01:57:20,607
What?

911
01:57:20,708 --> 01:57:22,301
But you saved her.

912
01:57:23,377 --> 01:57:26,540
You interfered with our fate.

913
01:57:26,647 --> 01:57:29,582
She'll cause you grief someday.

914
01:57:29,684 --> 01:57:33,746
I know you well.
1 advise you to think well.

915
02:00:23,591 --> 02:00:26,925
Toichi. Are they ready?

916
02:00:37,271 --> 02:00:39,831
I don't know...

917
02:00:39,940 --> 02:00:42,409
Maybe you can do better?

918
02:00:52,853 --> 02:00:53,752
Oh, well.

919
02:00:55,289 --> 02:00:57,223
I'll come back for them.

920
02:01:42,503 --> 02:01:43,766
It's time.

921
02:01:44,939 --> 02:01:48,773
I'll go see the doctor.

922
02:02:31,919 --> 02:02:36,481
Old Toichi is kind of losing it.

923
02:02:40,394 --> 02:02:43,056
Maybe you're a burden to him now.

924
02:02:48,369 --> 02:02:53,034
Surely you don't want
to stay here forever?

925
02:02:54,742 --> 02:02:58,736
It's time you left.
It'd be good for both of you.

926
02:03:05,753 --> 02:03:10,020
I never told you,
but I went to your village.

927
02:03:10,124 --> 02:03:11,922
Toichi asked me to.

928
02:03:13,494 --> 02:03:17,124
Was it Ichi-nomiya?

929
02:03:20,634 --> 02:03:23,535
What I heard didn't really add up.

930
02:03:27,708 --> 02:03:29,699
You know what I'm saying?

931
02:03:34,048 --> 02:03:35,413
Let go.

932
02:03:40,855 --> 02:03:43,085
I can take care of you.

933
02:04:03,077 --> 02:04:06,980
You look pale.
I bet you're not eating well.

934
02:04:08,516 --> 02:04:09,779
Well...

935
02:04:14,155 --> 02:04:15,554
Toichi.

936
02:04:18,459 --> 02:04:20,655
You need to take it easy.

937
02:04:22,763 --> 02:04:25,733
It's bad to think too much.

938
02:04:28,602 --> 02:04:30,969
You'd lose your mind if you did.

939
02:04:33,040 --> 02:04:37,170
Life is short.
Might as well enjoy it.

940
02:04:37,478 --> 02:04:38,673
Right?

941
02:04:46,520 --> 02:04:48,784
You know why we reincarnate?

942
02:04:53,494 --> 02:04:56,088
We need to live many lives...

943
02:04:58,633 --> 02:05:01,125
to grow wiser.

944
02:05:04,038 --> 02:05:07,770
We're brought to this world to learn

945
02:05:07,875 --> 02:05:11,505
one thing before we depart.

946
02:05:11,612 --> 02:05:15,981
What you learn varies
from one person to another.

947
02:05:18,519 --> 02:05:21,113
You live to find that thing.

948
02:05:24,892 --> 02:05:28,795
And you cross a river
to move on to the next life.

949
02:05:31,699 --> 02:05:34,930
I know!
Since you're a boatman...

950
02:05:36,070 --> 02:05:39,802
you'll have no problem
crossing the Styx.

951
02:06:42,603 --> 02:06:43,866
Toichi.

952
02:06:48,609 --> 02:06:52,273
Toichi, I haven't seen you
for a long time.

953
02:06:54,915 --> 02:06:56,280
You went to town?

954
02:06:56,383 --> 02:06:59,353
Yes, I visited the doctor.

955
02:06:59,653 --> 02:07:01,178
Right.

956
02:07:04,959 --> 02:07:06,654
Sorry, Toichi.

957
02:07:09,096 --> 02:07:12,896
After this was built,
I hardly visit you.

958
02:07:13,000 --> 02:07:14,798
It's okay...

959
02:07:16,971 --> 02:07:19,906
All the villagers...

960
02:07:20,007 --> 02:07:24,672
Since we got the bridge
everyone acts so busy.

961
02:07:25,980 --> 02:07:30,315
Many villagers went to live in town.

962
02:07:33,420 --> 02:07:36,014
What will happen to us?

963
02:07:43,364 --> 02:07:47,096
I miss the times you took us across.

964
02:07:47,201 --> 02:07:52,298
Back when we weren't in a hurry
like we are now.

965
02:07:59,446 --> 02:08:00,880
Toichi...

966
02:08:03,918 --> 02:08:07,946
can you take me
out on your boat someday?

967
02:08:11,259 --> 02:08:12,818
Certainly.

968
02:08:51,064 --> 02:08:52,691
What happened?

969
02:08:55,002 --> 02:08:56,436
What is it?

970
02:09:15,122 --> 02:09:16,453
What happened?

971
02:09:22,296 --> 02:09:23,730
Tell me what happened!

972
02:09:34,375 --> 02:09:37,140
It won't get worse.

973
02:09:40,548 --> 02:09:43,745
It won't get worse than this.

974
02:09:45,253 --> 02:09:47,119
Calm down.

975
02:09:47,221 --> 02:09:51,180
I won't blame you for anything!

976
02:09:51,291 --> 02:09:53,919
You've done nothing wrong!

977
02:09:54,028 --> 02:09:58,022
<i>You just protected yourself!</i>

978
02:09:58,132 --> 02:10:00,897
You're not to blame!

979
02:10:03,237 --> 02:10:08,437
I'm not so righteous as to blame you!

980
02:10:09,510 --> 02:10:14,004
I'm just a selfish nobody!

981
02:10:14,115 --> 02:10:15,879
But I...

982
02:10:15,983 --> 02:10:17,883
thought...

983
02:10:21,822 --> 02:10:24,257
I could protect you.

984
02:10:29,163 --> 02:10:31,154
I wanted to...

985
02:11:38,899 --> 02:11:43,427
I've got nothing left here anyway.

